cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper discusses the use of unmanned aerial platforms equipped with base stations in cellular networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the management and optimization of the drone-cell network, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of software-defined networking and cloud computing also suggests a possible category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper mentions the potential for drone-cells to serve diversified demands, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
